'''Lenny Joseph''' (born 12 October 2000) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Nemzeti Bajnokság I|Hungarian]] club [[Ferencvárosi TC|Ferencváros]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Joseph began his senior career with  [[Le Puy Foot 43 Auvergne|Le Puy]] and the reserves of [[US Boulogne|Boulogne]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.francebleu.fr/sports/football/de-la-n2-au-fc-metz-la-belle-histoire-de-lenny-joseph-nouvel-attaquant-des-grenats-1624377056|title=De la N2 au FC Metz : la belle histoire de Lenny Joseph, nouvel attaquant des Grenats|date=22 June 2021|website=France Bleu}}</ref> After strong performances in the [[2020–21 Coupe de France]], he signed a professional contract with [[FC Metz]] in the summer of 2021.<ref name="Football Club de Metz 2021">{{cite web | title=Lenny Joseph rejoint les Grenats ! | website=Football Club de Metz | date=10 June 2021 | url=https://www.fcmetz.com/2020-2021/actualites/equipe-pro/lenny-joseph-rejoint-les-grenats | language=fr | access-date=8 August 2021}}</ref> He made his professional debut with Metz in a 3–3 [[Ligue 1]] tie with [[Lille OSC|Lille]] 8 August 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2021/08/08/france/ligue-1/fc-de-metz/lille-olympique-sporting-club-metropole/3525904/|title=Metz vs. Lille - 8 August 2021|website=Soccerway}}</ref>

===Ferencváros===
On 20 January 2025, Joseph was signed by [[Hungarian League]] club [[Ferencvárosi TC]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fradi.hu/labdarugas/elso-csapat/hirek/francia-szelsovel-erositett-bajnokcsapatunk |title=Francia szélsővel erősített bajnokcsapatunk |publisher=Ferencvárosi TC |date=20 January 2025 |language=hu}}</ref> On 9 May 2026, he won the [[2025–26 Magyar Kupa]] season with Ferencváros by beating [[Zalaegerszegi TE]] 1–0 in the [[2026 Magyar Kupa final]] at [[Puskás Aréna]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=9 May 2026 |title=Gundel-Takács tizenegyest védett, de Raemaekers a Fradi javára döntötte el a kupadöntőt |url=https://www.nemzetisport.hu/labdarugo-nb-i/2026/05/gundel-takacs-tizenegyest-vedett-de-raemaekers-a-fradi-javara-dontotte-el-a-kupadontot |access-date=10 May 2026 |website=Nemzeti Sport |language=hu}}</ref>

==International career==
Joseph was born in France to a Haitian father and DR Congolese mother.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/coupe-de-france/portrait-jouer-au-parc-un-reve-denfant-lenny-joseph-lamateur-devenu-pro-grace-a-la-coupe-abef847c-b09a-11ee-aa61-307337b06e99|title=PORTRAIT. « Jouer au Parc, un rêve d’enfant » : Lenny Joseph, l’amateur devenu pro grâce à la Coupe|date=7 February 2024}}</ref> He was called up for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] to represent [[Haiti national football team]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-15 |title=A Fradi támadója is ott lehet a vb-n – Lenny Joseph meghívót kapott a haiti válogatottba |url=https://m4sport.hu/labdarugas/magyar-foci/cikk/2026/05/15/a-fradi-tamadoja-is-ott-lesz-a-vb-n-lenny-joseph-meghivot-kapott-a-haiti-valogatottba/ |access-date=2026-05-16 |website=M4 Sport |language=hu}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Arnold |first=Jon |title=2026 Haiti World Cup roster: Complete 26-man team |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/soccer/worldcup/2026/05/15/haiti-national-team-fifa-world-cup-roster-official-squad/90065445007/ |access-date=2026-05-16 |website=USA TODAY |language=en-US}}</ref> He said in an interview with Fradi.hu that a dream would come true if he could play at the World Cup.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Lenny Joseph: Nekem is nagy álmom vb-n szerepelni |url=https://www.fradi.hu/labdarugas/elso-csapat/hirek/lenny-joseph-nekem-is-nagy-almom-vb-n-szerepelni |access-date=2026-05-16 |website=www.fradi.hu |language=hu}}</ref>

